> 'Palak' is Hindi for spinach, the iron-rich leafy green in this mildly spiced, creamy curry - not to be confused with 'saag', which means any kind of leafy greens! Chicken is the perfect vehicle for soaking up the delicious flavours.

Pour @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} to a #medium bowl{}.

Sprinkle over the @Plain Flour{1%tbsp} and @Salt{¼%tsp}. Toss together so the chicken is nicely coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the chicken until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

Meanwhile, clean out the chicken bowl. Once the chicken is crispy, transfer it to the (now clean) #bowl{} and set aside for later.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop back onto medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the garlic, @Korma Curry Paste{50%g} and @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}. Fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Next, stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Mango Chutney{40%g} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat.

Add the chicken back into the pan and simmer until the liquid has reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pour in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g} and @Butter{20%g}.

Stir the @Baby Spinach{40%g} into the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and remove from the heat. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the rice out between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the curry. Sprinkle on the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!